caption: Food was good.  Prices good. Service was not that good. Felt rushed.

I adore this place! They offer splendid meals, their menu is rich, The chief cook in that place is a real pro, I like very much trying all their food. The dishes are consistently good, the attitude towards the visitors  is good. I frequently visit this restaurant and I was never disappointed. Highly recommended.

Pizza is always really good, but we ordered a salad for the first time today and all of the lettuce was completely rotten! How could they serve that?!? Very disappointed! Definatly not "Elegant Fine Dining".

First time trying this restaurant...we are foodies & live in Medford. Got a gift card for our anniversary...it was delicious! Hubby got shrimp & scallop fra diavolo, I got seared scallops with spinach over linguine with limoncello cream sauce..both delicious! Our little guy got buttered pasta from kids menu. Our only complaint is we thought it was pricey 10 for a kids meal? No drink included? Lemonade was 3.50! Our son got a kids size and I got one..no apps-  bill was $80. $100 with tip. Friendly owner & waitstaff & the history/bank vault was cool.
Nice experience all around. Good, friendly service.  Food & drink was good.  All good.
Tha food was amazing , the service was impeccable.  Renee was friendly and attentive . Our food came out in a more than timely manner and the price was great . All in all this is a great place to eat
Wonderful delicious food. The hostess needs to be dressed appropriately for a nice place like this.
The food and service was amazing.

Jumped In For Some Appies! Antipasto,Arancini,Mozzarella and Fried Calamari! Service was Good.Owner Also There(Very Nice/Cordial. The Calamari Was Quite Possibly the Best I've Ever Had(To Date) Tender,Seasoned Perfectly and NOT over Cooked! Antipasto was Decent;but Rather Bland on a Underwelming Presentation Plate! All Else Very Good! Solid 4.5 Stars.
Terrible service, bar stools were wobbly and seat cushions were torn.  Music was good.  Should be "the place to go" in Medford Square, but it is not.
Excellent food, service, ambiance...check out the Groupon!
Amazing Food. Great bar and wait staff. Excellent!!!
Used a Groupon for dinner here. The dinner was fine but the service was slow since our server was't very attentive and preferred watching tv at the bar instead .

This place is my favored. I eat in plenty of restaurants but to this one I keep coming back again and again. The stuff is very attentive and the cuisine they offer is so fresh and tasty. I would always prefer to have a good meal in this restaurant. I recommend this place with pleasure.
Party of 7 everyone enjoyed their dish,as long as it was Italian. Wait staff seemed rushed.
Awesome gluten free options! I really enjoyed being able to have Chicken Parm again
Chicken parm is my go to here

Excellent food, large servings. Parking on the street and large parking lot around back. The wait staff was helpful and polite. Medford square is crowded area, but with parking around back this had easy access and is strongly recommended.

On my second visit I was disappointed.  The menu had changed so I ordered garlic bread which was very good.  But the entree of pasta bolognese lacked flavor and had large chunks of meat that I chose to avoid.   A friend ordered eggplant which she shared with me and it was good but not great.   The dessert offerings did not intrigue us at all.   I will not be returning

Well I love everything Italian. I was very dissapointed with the food. The lamb was gross and the pasta that my sister ordered was bad. It was very pricey for the food we ordered. Not my type of place to go back
Good food and service.

One of the better gluten free restaurants in the Medford area. I’m partial to the chicken piccata with gluten free pasta. The interior is nice, relaxing and has a local feel. It’s not for everyone. My friends have mixed feelings but I’m more limited so value my time here.
Decent Italian food. Very friendly service. The bank vault is an amazing but of history.
Great place
We were there for a Christmas dinner for 11 in the vault.  The appetizers and entrees were enjoyed by all.  Irene was our excellent server. Many who live near plan to have lunch there soon.
Food is ok, service was slow
Great food an service
Eh. Good staff but pretty mediocre food. What Italian restaurant has sashimi and Sriracha wings??

I pop into this place every once in a while to meet a friend for some dinner and drinks and it's been consistently good over the years.  Staff are always very friendly, service is fast and the dishes I've tried are amazing.  Last night I had butternut squash ravioli, my friend had garlic bread and scallops and we devoured our food.  So good!  I'll continue to visit this place when I'm in the area.
I wont go back!!! The eggplant parm was all crust coating and the thinnest slice if eggplant ever possible!!! Service was slow...
Great local spot

Our Food and Service was excellent last night for my Brother’s Birthday Dinner! Our server Georgia was fabulous and friendly! Thank you Georgia for making my Brother’s birthday dinner the best ever!!!
Service was excellent!! Food and wine is overpriced,  menu was outdated but never changed.  Not the best experience overall.
Food is decent. Staff is very friendly. Service is slow. Trivia night is lots of fun, Kevin is great. Food kind of pricey

Clean, cute, ornate setting that made for fun times for the people I saw in the restaurant. I got the Shrimp and Scallops Fra Diablo that was the best I've had in the numerous times I've ordered it in. Scallops were perfectly cooked, like eating butter. The pasta was a spiral kind cooked just right. But the sauce was the winner. Chunks of tomato, parsley and basil with a taste I couldn't pin down. If you want Italian, come here!

We dined at the Medford location Saturday night before heading to a show. We were a table of eight and everyone was quite disappointed with the quality of food that was brought to the table and the lengthy delay.  Appetizers, although somewhat decent in flavor, were small for the price and cold. We finally received our entrees 60 minutes after we sat down and two of the eight entrees were extremely over cooked (steak tips). It was actually quite surprising that they made it out of the kitchen.  We were told that the over cooked meals were being removed from our bill, but actually were not. We didn’t make a fuss about it and paid for the two meals which were inedible, since the waitress was so horrified.  Apparently there was a great shortage of glasses too, as we had to ask servers times for the drinks we ordered - we were told, “glassware are being washed”. How does a restaurant run out of glassware during dinner time? Never experienced something like that before.  The wait person serving us was very friendly, professional, kind and courteous, however seemed very disorganized and quite embarrassed due to the quality of food items we were served and the lengthy time it took to get us our orders.  I’m not Gordon Ramsey nor do I work for Phantom Gourmet, but I would consider myself a man of taste and this place lacked quality on multiple levels, especially for the price you pay here.  Dine somewhere else!
Food was great! Service was slow.
Awesome, great food, great service!
Amazing tenders. Excellent menu

I enjoyed chicken pasta and broccoli for lunch. It was fantastic! Karli, my server and bartender was pleasant, professional and had such a welcoming and friendly demeanor. The service was fantastic. I enjoyed every sip of my cosmo and every bite of my lunch. Loved the delicious, warm bread and oil too. Will absolutely reccomend and return! Thank you, Karli!

This is a mixed review. I went here with my sister and we had completely different experiences. I ordered off of their gluten free menu and the food was amazing. Everything was tasty and well seasoned. On the flip side, my sister ordered pasta (not gluten free) and said it was terrible. She eats pasta like no other and loves the stuff, so it was really really bad. The noodles looked very yellow and were all clumped together; she says they were tasteless and she could not finish them. I am unsure if this restaurant is worth the price they ask for their food.
Good food, good service , good drinks
Excellent service and everything I've ordered has been good.

This place is just ok, I have been in here several times and I never seem to get good service. Its like their doing you a favor. I have been in the industry for 41 yrs. Of coarse, I never tell anyone that while dinning. It used to be my wifes favorite resturant, until she started working in the industry. Now,unfortunately she knows what a Resturant is supposed to be run like so she dosent go in there any more. I have given them enough chances. Its always the same experience. Not quite what we ordered, to oily, to greasy, undercooked over cooked. Its just a very i consistent experience. Too bad we live a block away.
Very delicious food. Quality ingredients.

Last stop on vacation is an overnight stay in Medford. Having satisfied my seafood urge, I opted to go with an Italian meal. Salvatore's was within walking distance of the hotel, so I stopped in. Five star service along with a five star entree of linguine and meatballs and impeccable bread made for a great experience! A shame I don't live in Medford, or I'd be there every day!
Stopped in for a beer. Great staff and atmosphere. Well be back to try the food!

Met friends at the. And and the bartender was super nice and attentive, tried to get a table for better interactions and was asked if everyone in the party nm would be eating, other wise the server wouldn't allow us the table. Finally got the table and after we ate and had drinks the server was absurdly rude, grabbed the signed checks from our table and walked away without even a "have a. Ice night." Brought us the check and boxes before asking if we were all set. Had an attitude with us the entire time. There was no wait, the place was dead and no reason to. Other us have a table either. So strange.
Ok
Awesome food, excellent service.

Not open. Our guess is that they're on their summer hours now (which are posted on the door but not dated) but there was nothing telling us that when planning our trip - I drove from Hartford & my celiac friend drove from Maine. Disappointing for sure.
Wonderful food amd service. Very rustic ambiance.

Food was delicious.   Chicken Parmesan plate was ridiculously large for one person to eat.  Food came out quick and hot for our party of 20+.  Staff was friendly.   Good size parking lot out back was helpful as well.  Would recommend!

We went there before going to a stand up show  at the Cavalier theater as we wanted to get a drink and a little dessert.  We got seated pretty quickly near the bar. They had a live DJ there playing great tunes to match the crowd. Most people at the venue seemed like they were there for the show as well. I ordered the recommended espresso martini. I was okay. The quality was not of a drink that should be recommended though as you can taste the cheep vodka and was not very smooth. We got a chocolate dessert. It was okay as well. Places like these typically do not make their own, but by a prepackaged dessert and sell them out of the box with a garnish on it.  The service was okay as well. It a great place to go get drinks, but prob not the best for a quality late night food.  Prices were decent.  Next time I go will prob be for drinks and fried apps before the show.  As we were leaving a large crowd stated pouring in from the early show to get drinks.

Today i came with my friend for drinks and food ..anyways terrible service..margarita tasted like some cheap tequila, it  was disgusting...our bartender i believe her name is susan whose is tatted up and really she looked like she dont know a dime about customer service..overall unfriendly service..i only came because i used to come here all the times when i lived in medford sq and mathew was the bartender but god damn one of my worst mistake by coming by just to get disappointed. Never again if ur younger then 30. This place is just for old italian couples now.
My waitress Jackie made my experience very pleasant. I enjoyed the baked haddock with a couple bloody Mary's. Fun night conversing with her. Fun attitude, great energy level.
Great place, great food.. The Vault is Awesome.
Best Italian food around! Huge portions and a great price!

I love Sal's, but I had an inexcusable experience recently. I went in on a Wednesday night, and was pretty much the only table not at the bar. I ordered my drink, and my date was still deciding so the waiter went to get mine while she was looking. We then waited almost a half hour, and the waiter never came back. We got no explanation as to what happened, so we left after not even getting bread or water to the table. I can't explain the rationale at all.  This was my only bad experience here, and it's really a shame. Ive had a great night every other time I've gone...

Nice atmosphere.  Really enjoyed chicken Alfredo, very creamy.

Ugh... Such a poor experience. First the good...one star for the calamari appetizer and one star for the good pour of bourbon for the price. The bad... No draft beer as the fridge was broken, out of the better bottled beer therefore with only bud/bud light, etc left.  My wife had to send her cocktail back as it wasn't drinkable. Many, many, many items on the menu weren't available and we weren't told till we ordered. Our meals were blah... Neither of us finished what we ended up with.
Bartenders are great

While I was a little annoyed at the fact that people who came in after us were seated before we were, the service by our waitress and the food more than made up for the minor inconvenience of waiting to be seated. The food is to die for, especially the calamari appetizer. The pasta with my ridiculously tender veal parm was cooked perfectly, not mushy or overcooked at all. My fiance got the steak tips and they were delicious! The marinade they use is mouthwatering, the tips were tender and flavorful, and everything reheated well the next day. Will definitely be going back!
I've never actually eaten here because I'm always on my way to my accountant when I stop in but the vibe is great, the drinks are great and the food looks great from across the room.
Portions we're great as was the food!

Trivia night, always fun. Kevin is the best !!!

Great place for drinks! The atmosphere is great and it was one of the first places to have a full bar once Medford was no longer a dry town.  That's about it because the food is only mediocre for the price. You are essentially paying for drinks and atmosphere.
Our waitress Ashley was the best and the food is amazing. I highly recommend this place
Place is great. Georgia our server is awesome. Go there, you will love it!

Visited here for a wedding rehearsal dinner this past weekend and it was a wonderful experience. Food was amazing and HUGE portions. Staff was prompt and courteous, especially MARK (the bartender)! He was the best. DJ they had was also awesome. Will definitely make a trip back here if we are ever in town. Thanks!

Beer was served in a broken bottle, took 20 minutes to get a beer and another 10 to replace the broken bottle. Food took upwards of an hour. Dont bother. Good personality behind the bar but truly awful service all around. Plan on spending the entire afternoon and night if you want 2 beers and a pizza.

Service was terrible. Order for 4 people took over an hour. Pizza was the best but the greens on top was not the arugula as the menu said. Waitress was apologetic but the poor service put a damper on the evening. May have given a better review if they would have provided 4 cannolies to go.
It is a great place for a date night!
Favorite place in Medford. Boston sunset drink and great food

The food is good. I really liked the scallops Limoncello and requested that pasta be added so I could have as a main. The server tried her best to discourage this saying the upcharge would be too much. However next time I will insist. The chicken picatta was good but the scallops are better. Real Gusto across the street serves excellent pasta.
Great service
Reasonable prices and good food. Great for a low key local eatery but nothing outstanding. If your looking for a good Italian place in the medford area, this won't do you wrong.
This was my first time in this area and we picked Salvatore’s just based upon reviews. It was fantastic food, great service and good atmosphere.
Welcoming, friendly, great crowd..excellent food.

Came here for a wedding rehearsal dinner. It was a catered event. They had several options available, and a of it was pretty dang good. I especially enjoyed the chicken marsala, and meatballs. They finished the meal off with a couple of deserts, including canolli. I would like to go back and see what the full menu offers sometime.

Had a meeting in Medford. Asked the local lawyer we met with and he recommended it. We went there for lunch. My wife had the salad with grilled chicken. I had the chicken caciatore. They were delicious.
Excellent food, great service,  nice atmosphere.

We asked the waitress to replace it please. But the second set of glasses came dirt again. So we left could trust the hygiene of the place anymore.

We went there for first time last night. Very disappointed. My girlfriend ordered haddock picatta and got chicken picatta. So my meal got cold while waiting for them to make her haddock picatta as originally ordered.  Never a visit from manager with apology. Waiter just shrugged it off as no big deal.  I asked for cheese for my pasta and it never came.  Also, we ordered caprese salad and it came with JUST 1 drop of olive oil and no salt or pepper as shown on menu. To top it off, the bill had both chicken picatta and haddock picatta on the bill. Very pricey, poor service, will not return. Too many other better choices in the area. Do not waste your money there.
Not impressed. Food was average. Service was ok.

Got take out tonight. Had the steak tip dinner and a chicken parm dinner with a small cheese pizza and the bruchetta flatbread. Outstanding on all fronts. Imagine ordering steak tips medium rare for takeout, and when you get home, they're pink! Girls upfront were amazing. They stayed smiling and were always polite. I noticed many rude and impatient patrons making comments to them that were unnecessary and uncalled for.  This place has always put forward their best dish for everyone and deserves a better rate than they get.
Busy, noisy, fun, happening place

Food came out fast, but the service is sub par.   I asked for tomatoes and olives on my salad and didn't get them.   The bartender didn't even recognize until I said something and was half done with the salad.   I was the only guy at the bar and in the restaurant at that time.  Would I come back sure, but not sit at the bar for I would like my food ordered correctly if I'm paying $30 for lunch.

My wife and her mother and I attended Salvatore's on Saturday before the Nutcracker. The downtown location was booked so we decided o try the Medford location. The place is very nice and charming. The reason for the low review was because of the food. I go to a restaurant for the food and not the decor. If they are going to charge the prices that they do, please get the food somewhat right.  I ordered that evening's steak special which was a New York Strip on a bed of risotto. The steak was rubbery and filled with gristle. If you don't know what that is , it is cartilage running throughout the steak. I live for a good steak and was very disappointed with this showing.

If you want great service, food and drinks....u must come to Salvatores in Medford. 5 stars in my book.

This place is awesome. Great food, service, and atmosphere. With some "very" interesting history to it. Highly recommend it and we will be back there again for sure!
I like the bank vault in the back converted into a dinning room. Crazy cool. I want to eat in there!

Home made raviolis and the best chicken parmesan around.
Good quality food, nice decor. We had a company party with buffet but the bartender was nice.
Best wait staff around! Great location, easy parking

Great food at reasonable prices.  Enough vegetarian options for the vegetarians in our party.  The service is always excellent.  The parking lot in the rear can fill up at busy times, which is an issue.

This turned out to be an excellent choice for our out-of-town party of five. We all shared a wonderful appetizer which was a sampler plate, it was amazing. I had the Chicken Marsala which was out of this world. Then also tasted the Steak Tips which was an equally delicious dish. For dessert, we had the gelato. We all enjoyed our waitress with her Boston accent and the overall quaint neighborhood atmosphere environment in this restaurant.
The pizza is enormous!
Great Italian food in Medford square. Parking is available behind the restaurant. Good beer and wine selection. Have never had a bad meal. It is drafty and can be cold for the ladies.
Delicious upper scale Italian food in a cool and cozy setting.

The Waitres Paige  was awful! Had to leave after not being ask what we wanted to order after 15 min . We were on our lunch hour . Have had lunch there many times with out this issue. Won't go back if she is going to be our waitress.
Solid food and service.
Good food, nice place for a date. The live music on Saturday made it seem a bit crowded but with the extra space it's a good spot for Italian.

(Translated by Google) Nice restaurant, very good decorated. Great and tasty dishes, good wine list. Good service .  (Original) Restaurante legal, muito bem decorado. Ótimos pratos e saborosos , boa carta de vinhos. Bom atendimento .
Service is hit or miss... Lately miss

Love Salvatore's Medford.  Food is good, drink is good.  If you are lucky enough to get Georgia as your server you will have an A plus experience.  Great place.  Trivia on Thursday is also great. Kevin does trivia how it should be done!

I've been to Salvatores several times.  I have to say I have never been disappointed with either the service or the menu.  I find the wait staff and bartenders to be personable, pleasant, attentive and willing to please.  Although I go to the North End for the authentic Italian - Salvatores is a great local bar, with a great bar menu and drinks.  They have a DJ there on Friday and Entertainment on Saturdays in the bar area but it doesn't intrude on the overall atmosphere.
Absolutely delicious pizza, wonderful tasting crust and great service.

Hit or miss on a grand scale. Luckily lat bunch of times has been a hit. Good pizza. AWESOME MENU. Nice wine list. Good a little pricey but not wine. Needs new tvs st bar for sporting events. Service very hit or miss. Great ambiance and love the live music.

Just had a luncheon there for a party of 25 people with various sandwiches and wraps and a big tossed salad, everything was delicious.  Our waiter James was very accommodating to our party. A great big thank you to Salvatore's for a successful time!

To say I am dissatisfied would be an understatement, my wife and I went here for the first time last night and had a terrible experience. I ordered the scallops and shrimp fra diavolo and as soon as it was put in front of me it smelled awful, I lifted the plate and noticed it was obviously the scallops, they were bad. I made the waiter aware of this and he couldnt of been nicer and said I will get the manager. The manager comes and right away she says before I said anything that the seafood was brought in "fresh" daily and basically acted like I couldnt possibly be correct. She just kept saying how fresh her seafood was. Needless to say, we wont be going back to Salvatores.

Came in here for their Monday wireless lunch.  They give you 1/2 off if you give them your cell phone and eat disconnected.  The lunch menu has lots of options from pizza's, to pasta and apps and salad's.  The staff is friendly and the food is flavorful.  They give you bread with oil to start which is also nice.  I would go back again.

(Translated by Google) Dinner with the family when we arrived in Boston. Impeccable service. Plates generous. Very good. I would return without hesitation.  (Original) Souper en famille lors de notre arrivé à Boston. Service impeccable. Assiettes généreuses.  Très bon.  J'y retournerais sans hésitation.
Awesome pasta dishes. Recommend.

two of the four entrees were horrible. one was not eve close to what the menu described it to be (gnocchi with goat cheese and sausage) I guess they forgot to put in the two key ingredients (cheese and sausage). one other entree was prepared so poorly the chef made us choose another entree, which turned out to be horrible. risotto dish...delivered cold to our table and again not matching the description on the menu. They even managed to give us a poor antipasto appetizer. four pieces of Italian cold cuts, and two pieces of dried up cheese. (no greens or dressing came with this)....not a cheap place to dine, you would think they would offer the quality of food that the price dictates. Stay away, there are at least three better options for a delicious meal in Medford than Salvatore's...try Boccelli's, Rasso's or, heck even the food at Pastalina's is far better.

I thought the food was a low 4 star rating, but the service makes up for it.  The mussels were great - perfectly cooked and a great sauce. We got extra bread and sopped up all that goodness.  Braised pork belly in the carbonara sounds like a good idea... but the traditional bacon provides a texture and flavor that they just didn't get to. The gnocchi dish was also a little too sweet and heavy... overall, the carbonara dish (normally a heavy dish) needed a little more oomph and the gnocchi (normally a lighter dish) needed a little less - they hit that middle too much.  Nonetheless, it was a good experience. I'd consider going back if I were in the area.
Food and service was very good.  Prices were very reasonable.  I liked the Decor it was comfortable and friendly.  Would recommend to friends and family and will return
